page.title: 13ECOLOGY PLANT SURVEY FIELD B
page.content: The second field surveyed is a potato field on the same map ref.86,33 on exactly the opposite,West side of the same road. 44 plants & 7 trees or shrubs were found. Scentless mayweed, Creeping thistle, Field speedwell, Pineapple weed, Shepherds purse, Knotweed, Hogweed, Dogrose, Blackberry, Ivy, Brome grass, Hawthorn, Ash, Goosegrass, Sycamore, Red dead nettle, Poppy, Hedge parsley, Nettle, Forget me not, Scorpion grass, White bryony, Chickweed, Fat hen, Hedge mustard, Stinking mayweed, Persicaria, Field pansy, Goosefoot, Scarlet pimpernel,Spotted persicaria, Rosebay willow herb, Gorse, Bindweed, Black bryony, Elder, Great willowherb, Cranesbill, Cut leaved cranesbill, Hedge bedstraw,Groundsel, Ragwort, Small flowered willowherb, Dog daisy, Greater hedge bedstraw,white clover,
